State.Author: Hrnchamd
State.Description: Patches bugs in the Morrowind program, which cannot otherwise be fixed by editing scripts or data files. Cures many crash and save corruption problems.
State.Name: Morrowind Code Patch

State.Author: Hrnchamd
State.Description: Morrowind Graphics Extender XE; allows Morrowind to render distant views, scenery shadows, high quality shaders and other features. Mods the vanilla engine, not usable with OpenMW.
State.Name: MGE XE

Original.Name: TESCS fixed for Morrowind Steam GOTY v1.6.1820 and Bethesda.net - VO-42196-1-6-1820-1553736429.zip

State.Author: papill6n
State.Description:
This package replace the missing files and allow the use of the TES: Construction Set with the Steam version of Morrowind Game of the Year Edition ( v1.6.1820), GOG and the Bethesda.net Launcher version.

Ce mod ajoute les fichiers manquants et permets d'utiliser le TES Construction Set avec la version de Steam, GOG et de Bethesda.net de Morrow
State.Name: TESCS fixed for Morrowind Steam GOTY v1.6.1820 - GOG - Bethesda.net - English and French TES Construction Set

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description: Adds a slaver and his hand to Tel Aruhn to showcase the armor. Can also buy the armor and cloth from the proper merchants in Tel Aruhn and Tel Branora.
State.Name: Telvanni Armors - Slavers and Wizards

State.Author: MorrowGoblins
State.Description: THE ARMOR OF ERGALLA!!!!
State.Name: Ergallas Breton Armor

State.Author: natinnet
State.Description: This mod for TES III: Morrowind adds to the game an incomplete set of glass armor: helm, shield and pauldrons. You can find them in one of the Temple strongholds guarded by Buoyant Armigers.
State.Name: Buoyant Armiger Armor

State.Author: Danae
State.Description: The Imperial and Tribunal Shrine's blessings will also cure your companions.
State.Name: Mass Cure

State.Author: Billyfighter
State.Description: Adds three animated floating Astrology shrines across Vvardenfell which give temporary boosts to the player. Speed, attack and magicka.
State.Name: Astrology Shrines

State.Author: OperatorJack and RedFurryDemon
State.Description: A lua-based framework for creating new, fully functional magic effects. Currently adds 109 new magic effects.
State.Name: Magicka Expanded

State.Author: autumn
State.Description: 230+ NPCs are given unique spells, enchantments, and items, to make Morrowind deadlier AND more varied. Faction bosses, Artifact owners, and Daedric cultists have been given customized, flavorful make-overs to become more difficult AND more memorable. Players are encouraged to carry resists, dispels, restores, and prepare ahead for big fights.
State.Name: MDMD - More Deadly Morrowind Denizens

State.Author: RingComics
State.Description: Free Nirie Selleth from slavery and help her find the Redoran Blessed Lute of the Warrior Poet.
State.Name: The Redoran Bard

State.Author: Phoenix Rime
State.Description: The modification makes the disposition of NPCs towards the player more realistic. Increases the number of amazing voice lines you'll hear per game.
State.Name: Real Disposition

State.Author: Kalamestari_69
State.Description: This mod allows you to fight and bet for fights in the Vivec's Arena, just like in the the Imperial City Arena in Oblivion.
State.Name: Welcome to the Arena

State.Author: Ketsugo
State.Description: A brief one-cell grotto dungeon intended for lower level characters involving a smuggler's nest situated in the Bitter Coast, on the southern side of the road leading to Vivec from Seyda Neen.
State.Name: The Flooded Grotto

State.Author: Lika0n
State.Description: This mod adds several nordic medium sized islands at the northest of Solstheim.
State.Name: Vanheim

State.Author: Cross-Project Coordination
State.Description: Culminating from a year of hard work, Tamriel_Data contains a data unified file structure spearheaded by Project Tamriel and Tamriel Rebuilt as the first adopter.
State.Name: Tamriel_Data

State.Author: Tamriel Rebuilt Team
State.Description: Tamriel Rebuilt is a large fan project that aims to complete development of The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind by reconstructing the world to include the province’s mainland, through the study of creation of lore, and preservation of the game’s creative vision and direction.
State.Name: Tamriel Rebuilt

State.Author: Ancestral Ashkhans
State.Description: The lost "Crystal City" of Massama has been discovered by a desperate group of escaped slaves. Through a series of quests, players will learn some of the secrets behind The Curse of Massama while trying to keep the separate factions from killing each other over the raw glass they've mined.
State.Name: Secrets of the Crystal City

State.Author: Malbogatra
State.Description: A new look for Sheogorad - a gloomy, deserted and abandoned region on the edge of the inhabited world.
State.Name: Spines of Madness

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This simple mod provides an in-game HUD element as the game approaches critical memory limits.
State.Name: Memory Monitor

State.Author: Vayatir
State.Description: A small, basic apartment within the Almas Thirr canton to serve as a player house. Lots of storage!
State.Name: Almas Thirr Player Home for Tamriel Rebuilt

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: QwertyQuit - ErwintheGerman
State.Description: The mod adds a personal quest for Master Aryon and expands his personality.
State.Name: The Wizard's Affair

State.Author: Seneca83
State.Description: Bthanchend is a large Dwemer city that connects all the Dwemer ruins under red mountain into one city. This allows players to get to any Dwemer ruin within Red Mountain without going back outside. The city is named after the last Dwemer ruin within Red Mountain not controlled by Dagoth Ur.
State.Name: Bthanchend

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Adds Secret Master lockpicks, probes, and alchemy apparatus to the game.
State.Name: Tools of the Secret Master

Original.Name: Solstheim Tomb of the Snow Prince-46810-2-2-2-1614593632.zip

State.Author: TOTSP Team
State.Description: ToTSP's goal is to improve the graphical fidelity, environmental design, and gameplay of the Bloodmoon DLC's to a level that is consistent with modern Tes3 mod projects, such as Tamriel Rebuilt and Project Tamriel.
State.Name: Solstheim - Tomb of the Snow Prince

State.Author: The Wanderer
State.Description:
Find the secret entrance in the Governor's Hall in Caldera.

Enter the lost rooms but you will have to  solve the puzzle to escape.
State.Name: Lost Rooms

State.Author: AlandroSul
State.Description: Five new witchhunter-themed quests in Balmora.
State.Name: The Witchhunter of Balmora

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description: Adds armor based on concept art by MK.
State.Name: Daggerlad

State.Author: mort
State.Description:
This mod is intended to rebalance the Tribunal expansion in a variety of ways, most importantly by editing the stats of creatures and npcs.

This mod rebalances Tribunal as if it shipped with Morrowind.
State.Name: Tribunal Rebalance

State.Author: Billyfighter
State.Description: Join a fully playable guild and gain ranks to the top. The Astrologians are a small scale guild, with just a handful of guild members started by an Altmer named Nelangoth, who was previously part of the Mages Guild and still holds ties to them. Includes several new dungeons, items, quests and locations. Designed for maximum compatibility.
State.Name: Astrologian's Guild

State.Author: globemallow
State.Description: Dive for secrets and uncover the mysteries of the Cliffracer's Roost in this short adventure.
State.Name: Troubled Waters

State.Author: deleted140146928
State.Description:
This is a Player Home high up in the sky above the Dunmer Stronghold Falensarano. It also contains some easter eggs to Retro Gaming on DOS. 



Cloud Storage Mod Compatibility in Optional File
State.Name: The Maniac's Mansion (OAAB required)

State.Description: Changes the 2 amulets from the aspect of strength and speed into a mask and boots respectively. Also includes a spear replacer.
State.Name: Hircine's Artifacts

State.Author: Kleidium
State.Description: This MWSE mod allows both NPC and Creature companions to level up with the player based on their Class/Creature Type (Class Mode) or specific player selected build settings (Build Mode). In Class Mode, you also have the choice of changing the Class/Creature Type your companions level as. Companions are also able to learn spells and abilities.
State.Name: Companion Leveler

State.Author: Danae and PikachunoTM
State.Description: Add 100 cards to the game, they can be found, bought or traded. upon completing a set, receive the corresponding album.
State.Name: Morrowind Trading Cards

State.Author: Hoju
State.Description: This mod combines two creatures that everyone will know and love: The Cliff Racer and the Greater Bonewalker. Enter.....the BONE RACER!
State.Name: Bone Racers

State.Author: Greatness7 - Kurpulio
State.Description: Replaces Shield spell visual effect.
State.Name: Spells Reforged - Shield

State.Author: Team Ancient Androids
State.Description: Set out on an adventure to Fort Stormwatch, a high security prison that has been taken over by the Inmates. The job is simple; rescue the hostages, kill the Inmates' leader and raise the front gate. But something far more sinister is happening... something that will test the Nerevarine's will and survival.
State.Name: Invasion of Stormwatch

State.Author: Greatness7
State.Description: Opens up an entire new facet of gameplay by granting the ability to use potions offensively, as poisons applied to your weapons. Supports all potions, including those added by other mods or crafted by the player. Additionally includes new HUD elements and various other improvements to the alchemy system as a whole.
State.Name: Poison Crafting

State.Author: Katya Karrel
State.Description: Discover a little secret of the Ashlander traders, who live near Iveri Llothri, the unlucky witch... This mod adds an interesting place to visit in the Grazelands, to the east of Zainab camp and to the south of Vos. Made for the Summer Modjam 2022.
State.Name: Thickle-Lo Grove

State.Author: Tamriel Rebuilt Team
State.Description: Tamriel Rebuilt is a large fan project that aims to complete development of The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind by reconstructing the world to include the province’s mainland, through the study of creation of lore, and preservation of the game’s creative vision and direction.
State.Name: Tamriel Rebuilt

State.Author: AliceL93
State.Description: Defeat a crew of bloodthirsty Sixth House pirates and take their treasure!
State.Name: Sixth House Pirates

State.Author: Mark
State.Description: A dungeon and quest mod based on my first character for Morrowind, made to commemorate Morrowind's 20th Anniversary. Start by stumbling into a recluse conjurer in his lair on an island in the Azura's Coast region, north of the Grazelands. Follow a short questline to discover the nature of his mysterious research and gain magical rewards.
State.Name: A Conjurer's Calling

State.Author: PrinceShroob
State.Description: Changes vampirism to work like in Oblivion and Skyrim; feed on your clan's cattle to decrease your vampirism stage. Most people won't recognize you as a vampire until you reach stage four vampirism.
State.Name: Simple Vampirism Overhaul

State.Author: ProfArmitage
State.Description: Go on a quest to find a mage's missing daughter.
State.Name: Rescue Mission

State.Author: JackimoffWackimoff
State.Description:
A short quest involving a strange gauntlet. Ask about rumors in Vivec to start.

For the 2023 modjam.
State.Name: The Hand

State.Author: Cross-Project Coordination
State.Description: Culminating from a year of hard work, Tamriel_Data contains a data unified file structure spearheaded by Project Tamriel and Tamriel Rebuilt as the first adopter.
State.Name: Tamriel_Data

Original.Name: Dura gra-Bol's House Reclaimed - And the Grab-All Gang-46772-2-2-1655926088.7z

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: This mod started as a simple house mod and expanded into an entire smuggling faction - while still allowing you to choose the high road and be rewarded for killing Dura as instructed. Get to work with Larrius Varro again as he sticks his nose into more of Vvardenfell's dirty business. Or choose the profitable path of a smuggler and climb the ranks.
State.Name: Dura gra-Bol's House Reclaimed - And the Grab-All Gang

State.Author: MTR
State.Description: This mod randomizes placement of Dwemer Puzzle Box. Made in regular mwscript, so it works in OpenMW too!
State.Name: mtrDwemerPuzzleBoxRandomizer - Randomizer for Location of Dwemer Puzzle Box within Arkngthand associated with Main Quest

State.Author: QueenOfTheSilence
State.Description: I add houses that are purchasable to the Mainland, AKA Tamriel Rebuilt
State.Name: Home Is Where the Mainland Is

State.Author: zdeadguy
State.Description: Tweaks, patches,  and random miscellaneous things compatible with OpenMW.
State.Name: ZDG WIP's and Misc

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: OAAB_Data is free-to-use asset repository for the Morrowind Community.
State.Name: OAAB_Data

State.Author: Danae Aurel
State.Description: Modular versions of WARES for Vvardenfell, Tamriel Rebuilt, Skyrim Home of the Nords, and Province Cyrodiil including items, traders, npcs, Hold it and containers.
State.Name: Wares Ultimate

State.Author: Celediel
State.Description: Stop friendly fire. Player companions can't damage the player, the player can't damage companions, and companions can't damage each other. Option to stop combat from occurring between friendly actors. That's it.
State.Name: No More Friendly Fire

State.Author: RandomPal and CyrianWarlord
State.Description: Lightweight mod that adds bandits in the wilderness
State.Name: Bandits

Original.Name: Sixth House Informant - The Monastery of Ishdad Ab-52883-FINAL-1684121126.zip

State.Author: SCH2266
State.Description: New quest featuring a medium sized sixth house base.
State.Name: Sixth House Informant - The Monastery of Ishdad Ab

State.Author: Wub
State.Description: One of the first things I noticed after looting my 10th smuggler cave and selling my 13x lock and gemfeeder scroll was a serious dearth of interesting scrolls available. So I created this mod to fix that.
State.Name: Expanded Smuggler Scrolls

Original.Name: Caldera Priory and the Depths of Blood and Bone-52898-1-1-1684511454.zip

State.Author: seelof and his minions
State.Description: Caldera Priory has been overrun by the Undead. Do you have the courage and the will to venture into the Depths of Blood and Bone and vanquish the ancient Evil that has taken hold of the lands above?
State.Name: Caldera Priory and the Depths of Blood and Bone

State.Author: Ruffin Vangarr
State.Description: This mod adds unique robes for each of the Telvanni councilors including Baladas and Uvirith, Each one holds a special powerful enchantment but it won't be easy to acquire.
State.Name: Telvanni Magister Robes

State.Author: classified
State.Description: Black ops equipment & graphics testing
State.Name: MCP Skunk Works

State.Author: NazoX9
State.Description: Morag Tong armor made by request.
State.Name: Morag Tong Armor

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description:
Adds 2 Redoran Watchman on guard in Gnisis



Update 1.1: Reworked the helmet and added a watchman in Maar Gan and Ald-ruhn
State.Name: Redoran Patrols - Gnisis

State.Author: Team Nordic Chefs
State.Description: On a strange island known to few as Crescent Moon Isle, a bloodbath awaits the player in a struggle for survival against a band of crazed assassins, all for the amusement of a few cultists hiding away in the shadows.  Partake in the slaughter with joy, or perhaps you believe in following the deity's actual wishes, hidden among the bodies...
State.Name: The Battle Rite of Mephala

State.Author: mort
State.Description:
This mod is intended to rebalance the Bloodmoon expansion in a variety of ways, most importantly by editing the stats of creatures and npcs.

This mod rebalances Bloodmoon as if it shipped with Morrowind.
State.Name: Bloodmoon Rebalance

State.Author: TES3 Community
State.Description: Patch for Purists is an unofficial patch for The Elder Scrolls III: Morrowind Game of the Year Edition that takes a more conservative approach about what it considers a "bug."
State.Name: Patch for Purists

State.Author: Team Ancient Androids
State.Description: Set out on an adventure to Fort Stormwatch, a high security prison that has been taken over by the Inmates. The job is simple; rescue the hostages, kill the Inmates' leader and raise the front gate. But something far more sinister is happening... something that will test the Nerevarine's will and survival.
State.Name: Invasion of Stormwatch

State.Author: Nazz
State.Description: This plugin adds many new spear and spear related weapons to the game. This includes new spears, halberds, and scythes using new textures and new models. Throwing spears that use the marksman skill, and one handed spears that mimic using your spear skill using scripting. Also includes two new shops where many of the new weapons can be bought.
State.Name: House of Spears

State.Author: osiris1333
State.Description: Maybe Therana isn't as delusional as she seems..
State.Name: A Telvanni Heist

State.Author: Kalinter
State.Description: Looming high over the hills of the northern Ashlands, the towers of Bal'laku are an awe-inspiring sight to behold.
State.Name: Bal'laku - The Lonely Towers

State.Author: Caeris and AliceL93
State.Description: Join the Talos Cult and embark on a conspiracy to kill the emperor.
State.Name: The Talos Cult Conspiracy

State.Author: jsp25
State.Description: This mod improves several vanilla dungeons aesthetically and/or expands them.
State.Name: Mines and Caverns

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description: Adds Telvanni Dust Adept armor to Morrowind. Based on Bethesda concept art.
State.Name: Telvanni Dust Adept

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description: A new armor shop in Vivec, St. Olms Waistworks. Bonemold, Racer Leather, some weapons and some cloth.
State.Name: Racer Dust Arms and Armor

State.Author: Ashstaar
State.Description:
Adds Sload merchants and Dunmer slavers to several locations of Morrowind. Includes a shop/smith in Molag Mar, Waistworks that sells new bonemold armor, weapons, and some clothing.



Update 1.2: New robed and masked sload models and sloadic items. A few new armor additions. A sload necromancer and zombie slaves are now inhabiting Arethan T
State.Name: Sload and Slavers

State.Author: elucidace
State.Description: This mod adds a bit of variety to the early helmet options in the form of three helmets that have been added to leveled lists, and one unique helmet hidden within the world.
State.Name: Netch Scout Helm

State.Author: Revacholiere
State.Description: Create dynamically-named trophies from any defeated enemy.
State.Name: Trophy Taker

State.Author: Sexy Sloads
State.Description: A mysterious book has fallen into your possession… How did it get there? Who does it belong to? Follow the clues, as you find yourself taken away by a detailed, multilayered story steeped in TES Lore.
State.Name: The Demon of Knowledge

State.Author: Sandman EJ-12 Danae
State.Description: A large collection of Armor
State.Name: Panoplies - Helluva Ways to Suit Up

State.Author: Juidius Xentao
State.Description: Each month on the 17th a skiff will appear in Suran. Onboard is a friendly ashlander looking to sell her wares.
State.Name: Suran Silt Skiff

State.Author: mort
State.Description: Makes the Sixth House, properly, the most difficult content in the game. Intended for use with my other rebalance mods.
State.Name: Beware the Sixth House (Sixth House Overhaul)

State.Author: Dark Sisterhood
State.Description:
Become the captain of your own ship, recruit crew members and acquire cargo to sell.

At long last, you may sail the Seas or row on the lakes and rivers!
State.Name: Sails and Sales

State.Author: Orion
State.Description: An extensive companion and quest mod that hooks onto Morrowinds Main Quest and offers a serious perspective to the world presented. Team up with a complex character with her own faults, hopes, and dreams. Discover another side to the Sixth House and its seedy connections. Make choices and roleplay who you want to be.
State.Name: Arvesa - An Armigers Tale

State.Author: Ortiee
State.Description: Each of the seven guilds three Great Houses in Vvardenfell now offer modest living quarters. Faction members now have somewhere to store a decent amount of stuff and a place to practice their skills while they work their way up through the ranks.
State.Name: Faction Living Quarters

State.Author: Kezyma
State.Description: This is a UI replacement for Morrowind, eventually intending to completely replace all UI elements in the game. I have packaged everything in a modular way so you can pick and choose which aspects of UI Remastered you'd like to use.
State.Name: Kezyma's UI Remastered

State.Author: VvardenfellStormSage Safebox and Rubberman
State.Description:
PART OF THE MW MAY MODATHON 2021



This mod adds a dead vampire hunter in the Galom Daeus Observatory, top level with some loot perfect for vamp or mage hunters... Requires MWSE if you want the crossbow pistol to fire only stakes...
State.Name: The Vampire Hunter's Legacy

State.Author: Morandir Nailo Celediel Danae
State.Description: A simple update and rebalance of Cannibals of Morrowind: traders won't sell their body parts anymore, nor can you make a fortune casually selling brains, more skulls to collect, updated graphics. You're welcome.
State.Name: Cannibals of Morrowind - Updated

State.Author: Billyfighter
State.Description: This is a quest mod for House Redoran members. It adds a new cave north-northwest of Skar, unlocked only to those ranked Oathman and above. Upon exploring the underground ecosystem and lost Redoran settlements buried by lava you'll find a new weapon and set of armor.
State.Name: Lost Redoran Relics

State.Author: Billyfighter
State.Description: An Imperial style set of ruins south and east of Suran. Included is a minor quest involving the Knights of Stendarr and the evil within the ruins.
State.Name: Duskmoth Ruins

State.Author: Billyfighter
State.Description: Pirates upon the shore of Azura's Coast, along with a market, tavern, and small cavern. Includes one short quest.
State.Name: Smuggler's Market

State.Author: MwGek
State.Description: A lighthouse has been added to the North-West of Dagon Fel. Meet Vigunn, the Nord lighthousekeeper.
State.Name: Dagon Fel Lighthouse

State.Author: seelof
State.Description: This mod redesigns the Library of Vivec from scratch to make it look and feel like a true library, with many books added from Tamriel_Data and OAAB_Data for you to read. There are also new NPCs for you to interact with, and two new quests that set you on the hunt for a unique book the resource for which was provided by RubberMan.
State.Name: ReadMe - Library of Vivec Overhaul

State.Author: mort
State.Description: Adds a custom real-time menu to pickpocketing and restores a formerly-useless mechanic.
State.Name: Pickpocket

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: A survival mod with hunger, thirst, tiredness, cooking, camping and temperature mechanics, as well as incredible new visuals, from seeing frost on your breath in cold weather, watching your food cook on the grill in real time, and seeing your camping gear displayed dynamically on your backpack.
State.Name: Ashfall - A Camping Survival and Needs Mod

State.Author: Nwahs and Mushrooms Team
State.Description: New lore friendly NPC in cities and villages. Customizable population density.
State.Name: MWSE Random NPC

State.Author: Danae
State.Description: A quaint underwater home with plenty of storage in the Sea of Ghosts.
State.Name: Restful Reef Refuge

State.Author: GrumblingVomit
State.Description: Adds a short quest for an underwater player home around Firewatch.
State.Name: Escapee's Rest

State.Author: TheDrunkenMudcrab Danae DimNussens
State.Description: Ius the Animal God has a questline full of adventure, drama, comedy, and romance, not to mention an artifact weapon, a companion, and more!
State.Name: Ius the Animal God

State.Author: Katya Karrel_Ruffin Vangarr
State.Description: This mod adds a house to the southwest of Tel Branora. Maybe you'll even find a cool dwemer helmet too!
State.Name: Arnchenzel - Dwemer Underwater House

State.Author: Rosynant
State.Description: What if a group of outcast Ordinators decided to join the Dissident Priests? This mod makes this interesting possibility come true by bringing Dissident Ordinators into the game. Features special armor and weapon, a micro-quest with unique dialogue, and an immersive addition to the Ministry of Truth. Part of the May Modathon Month 2023.
State.Name: Dissident Ordinators

State.Author: Team Massive Vomit - GrumblingVomit and MasssiveJuice
State.Description: Journey to a cold island and discover a plot to cover the world in eternal night.
State.Name: Secret of Vilmuhn

Original.Name: The Mysterious Affair of Sara Shenk-52968-1-0-1685303786.7z

State.Author: Juidius Danae
State.Description: In the quaint town of Caldera, the innkeeper, Shenk, becomes the centre of attention: the once-idyllic life of innkeeper Shenk takes a dark turn when his wife vanishes without a trace, leaving behind a trail of speculation and intrigue. Each step forward brings you closer to unravelling the enigma, but beware, for not all is as it seems.
State.Name: The Mysterious Affair of Sara Shenk

State.Author: Danae CutthroatMods Neoptolemus
State.Description: A large companion mod with 44 NPC companions, 21 creature companions, and quests that connects them.
State.Name: Friends and Frens

State.Author: natinnet
State.Description: The mod adds a few Sixth House themed stuff. You can find them in the Sixth House bases in Ashland and buy from a mysterious member of Camonna Tong.
State.Name: Sixth House Obisidian Weapon

State.Author: natinnet
State.Description: The mod adds to the game ebony dai-katana, katana wakizashi & tanto. They are scattered through different daedric ruins.
State.Name: Oriental Ebony Weapons

State.Author: Anroha
State.Description: The project is designed to add all the missing original weapons in the game, at the moment all weapons have been added from daggers to long spears, there are also crossbows and bows, they will also be added over time
State.Name: Weapons Expansion Project

State.Author: Ruffin Vangarr
State.Description: This mod adds various lore friendly Ashmasks, Menpos and face wraps with an MWSE script that allows them to be worn without hiding your hair or even taking up the helmet slot. (requires onion layers mod)
State.Name: Fashionwind - MWSE Masks and Facewraps

State.Author: The Madcrabs
State.Description: Adds a cozy new Hlaalu dock town at the mouth of the Odai River, as well as a few quests within the town. West of Seyda Neen, south of Balmora. Also marbles!
State.Name: Hla Odai

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Skills Module is a framework for MWSE+Lua mods that allows you to easily create new skills in Morrowind with just a few lines of code. Leveling and UI are handled automatically, with new skills added seamlessly into the stats menu.
State.Name: Skills Module

State.Author: ShadowMimicry and VitruvianGuar
State.Description: MWSE lua mod changing the mechanics of Sixth House attacking the player during the sleep.
State.Name: Disturbing Dreams

State.Author: Remiros
State.Description: Seek out an old hermit and explore the sunken shrine of Hermaeus Mora, deep within the Sea of Ghosts
State.Name: Prince of Fate

Original.Name: The Search for the White Wave-52301-1-2-1675822220.7z

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: A scientific expedition headed into the Sea of Ghosts has failed to report on their progress. An investigator from the Imperial Navy has been dispatched to locate the White Wave and is looking for a hand. Join his crew to unravel what happened to the White Wave in the frozen northern waters...
State.Name: The Search for the White Wave

State.Author: Caeris
State.Description: A mod that allows you to join the Dark Brotherhood on Vvardenfell, in a semi lore-friendly (it expands lore) and enticing story, that stays true to the vanilla vision.
State.Name: Vvardenfell Brotherhood

State.Author: Stripes
State.Description: A recently abandoned, vacant Velothi home located down the road of Sailen, in the Sacred Lands Region, Tamriel Rebuilt.
State.Name: Sailen Player Home for Tamriel Rebuilt

State.Author: Geonox  MasterSam  OperatorJack Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: Explore the Eye of Ariisiss, a beautiful ancient ruin, and claim it as your home.
State.Name: The Eye of Ariisiss Redux

State.Author: Team Gobblin Goblins
State.Description: Discover the Great Ossuaries of Ayem, Seht, and Vehk on the slopes of Red Mountain and their associated catacombs deep beneath the volcano.
State.Name: Memento Mori

State.Author: Grond1911
State.Description:
Find Aetherium in ore veins and upgrade old Dwemer equipment in the new Forge in Nchardumz.

- xander2077's New Dwemer Armor mod used as the base armor model.

- lautasantenni's Aetherium Armor and Weapons Compilation for Skyrim used as design inspiration.
State.Name: Aetherium Forging

State.Author: seelof and Greatness7
State.Description: This mod rebuilds and expands the Gnisis Eggmine complex from scratch, which includes the Eggmine, the Lower Eggmine, the Underground Stream, and Bethamez. It also adds a quest, which asks the player to investigate the origins of the tremors that have been plaguing the eggmine ever since the Dwemer ruin was uncovered. Features actual earth quakes!
State.Name: Of Eggs and Dwarves - Gnisis Eggmine and Bethamez Overhaul

State.Author: Grond1911
State.Description:
Find Aetherium in ore veins and upgrade old Dwemer equipment in the new Forge in Nchardumz.

- xander2077's New Dwemer Armor mod used as the base armor model.

- lautasantenni's Aetherium Armor and Weapons Compilation for Skyrim used as design inspiration.
State.Name: Aetherium Forging

State.Author: The Hive Mind
State.Description: Implementation of the official concept art drawing by Michael Kirkbride.
State.Name: Tales from the Ashlands - The Great Hive Baan Binif

State.Author: ProfArmitage
State.Description: Recover a stolen arcane tome from a renegade wizard and his magically animated puppet servants.
State.Name: Master of Puppets

State.Author: Caeris and Master Sam
State.Description: Dagoth Ur has been defeated, but the continued presence of the Sixth House still poses a threat to Morrowind. A lieutenant of the Tribe Unmourned has come out of the shadows in a sinister plot to resurrect Dagoth Ur.
State.Name: The Rise of the Tribe Unmourned

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Toggle lights on and off. Town lights turn off during the day. Lights no longer destroyed underwater. Lanterns aren't destroyed when they run out of fuel. Refill lanterns with candles and lamps with oil.
State.Name: The Midnight Oil - Lighting Overhaul

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: The concept behind the mod is to provide both an immersive experience by adding a uniform to mages guild members as well as to improve gameplay by providing a useful alternative to armor for mages; such as is offered in Skyrim. Many Mages Guild members will now wear the new robes and the player can acquire the robes through quests and purchase.
State.Name: Mage Robes

State.Author: Dreamy Dreamers
State.Description: Investigate a series of attacks on Tel Eurus, follow the clues to uncover the mastermind behind it. Level 10 or higher recommended.
State.Name: Investigations at Tel Eurus

State.Author: The Kwama Koalition of Denina Olaf Ring and TheDrunknenMudcrab
State.Description: Ask around about Latest Rumors in Maar Gan to find tell of a mine in peril. Bring forth its demise, or save it from financial ruin! Ever wanted to own a mine? Ever wanted to be friends with a kwama? This is the mod for you.
State.Name: Horror at Helvil Mine

State.Author: Danae and friends
State.Description: A voiced companion with quests, dungeons, new gear and unlockable features.
State.Name: Rishajiit - A Companion Quest Mod

State.Author: Scuttling Scribs
State.Description: A lore-friendly quest mod based on an in-game book brought to life, with dungeons, mind-bending puzzles, quests, Daedra, and the power to summon items from oblivion.
State.Name: Pimp My Shrine - The Daedric Legend of Vernaccus

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: The Crafting Framework is library that allows modders to quickly and easily implement complex crafting mechanics in Morrowind.
State.Name: The Crafting Framework

State.Author: VitruvianGuar
State.Description: Comprehensive modern day implementation of necromancy, using Skill Module, Magicka Expanded and Crafting Framework. Includes game mechanics overhaul, new quests and mysteries to solve, allowing to fully experience being the practicioner of a forbidden art of necromancy.
State.Name: Necrocraft - A Comprehensive Necromancy Gameplay And Quests Mod.

State.Author: natinnet
State.Description: Adds to the game dwarven & dwemer daikatana, katana, wakidzashi & tanto.
State.Name: Oriental Dwarven Weapon

State.Author: OperatorJack and Kurpulio and RedFurryDemon
State.Description: The third entry in the Magic Mechanics series, this mod adds new Oblivion-inspired visual effects and mechanics for the vanilla detection magic effects, as well as adds 7 new magic effects. It integrates those effects into new spells and distributes them in-game to spell vendors. It does all of this without requiring an ESP.
State.Name: MM - Enhanced Detection

State.Author: Caeris
State.Description: Begin a tale about the largest criminal organization in Morrowind, the Camonna Tong. Vye for power in all influences of society by working together with the likes of Orvas Dren, the Kingpin.
State.Name: Camonna Tong

State.Author: Stuporstar and Greatness7
State.Description: Now works with OpenMW! MWSE Graphic Herbalism harnesses the power of lua and mesh switchnodes, allowing this mod to be run without an esp or standard scripts. This dramatically optimizes performance compared to older graphic herbalism mods. It also comes with an mod configuration menu to allow you to change settings.
State.Name: Graphic Herbalism - MWSE and OpenMW Edition

State.Author: PeterBitt
State.Description:
Brings the Nirnroot to Vvardenfell.

A simple, non intrusive and bug free quest mod.
State.Name: A Strange Plant

State.Author: globemallow
State.Description: Made for Summer Modjam 2022! Meet One-Eye and Beela Fire-Beard, two Argonian pearl divers with a mysterious connection.
State.Name: The Pearl Divers

State.Author: Ferian
State.Description: This mod adds a Telvanni town on an island east of Solstheim.
State.Name: Tel Morgana

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: Drip adds Diablo 2 style loot to Morrowind. Unique weapons, armor, clothing and accesories are dynamically generated, with over a hundred unique modifiers and more than a million possible combinations. Chance to apply modifiers configurable in the MCM.
State.Name: DRIP - Dynamic Randomised Item Properties

Original.Name: Yul Marshee and the Visage of Mzund-51936-1-3-1668730246.7z

State.Author: The Provincial Privateers
State.Description: Embark on a set of unique adventures by helping out Yul Marshee complete her collection of lost treasures and assist her in building a bizarre Dwemer contraption.
State.Name: Yul Marshee and the Visage of Mzund

State.Author: Team Ceaseless Centurions
State.Description: This mod overhauls Fort Firemoth with new questline, enemies, atmosphere, and redone locations. Part of Morrowind Modding Madness 2022.
State.Name: Firemoth Reclaimed

State.Author: TES3 Community
State.Description: Makes unreadied weapons appear on the character's hip or back.
State.Name: Weapon Sheathing

State.Author: Markond
State.Description: An unusual Imperial fort to the farthest north of Sheogorad.
State.Name: Fort Ghostmoth

State.Author: Mika
State.Description: This is a very modest tiny and cozy priest's retreat in the catacombs of the temple of Balmora.
State.Name: The Priest's Hideout

State.Author: osiris1333
State.Description: Adds a high level necromancer boss somewhere hidden in the Molag Mar region. This was my way of implementing the Daedric Armor of St. Nerevar made by JyggalagJones.
State.Name: Thaerom The Awakened (High Level Boss)

State.Author: Merlord and Remiros
State.Description: Go Fletch adds a brand new Fletching skill to the game, utilising the latest skill and crafting frameworks in MWSE to fully integrate it into the vanilla UI.
State.Name: Go Fletch

State.Description:
Subtle Magic Glow replaces the \'plastic wrap\' around in-game magic items (those equipped by characters or on the ground) with less-obtrusive versions. There are three available: A more transparent version of the Bethesda original, one that is faint, but nonmoving, and one that is nonmoving but slowly fades in and out.

Texture replacer; no
State.Name: Subtle Magic Glow

State.Author: Noah Longsfellow
State.Description: This mod adds in Dawnbreaker as well as a full quest with a unique and lore friendly story, new npcs, and a shrine to Meridia.
State.Name: Dawnbreaker -  The Lady of Light

State.Author: Hrnchamd
State.Description: Adds interactive placement, rotation and wall mounting of items. Arrange gear, books and anything else you can pick up. Requires MWSE 2.1.
State.Name: Perfect Placement

State.Author: Kezyma - tewlwolow
State.Description: A project to fully voice Morrowind using ElevenAI and MWSE. Comes with an optional 'greetings-only' mode and is easily extensible to add compatibility with other mods with no knowledge of scripting or the CS and no additional esp.
State.Name: Kezyma's Voices of Vvardenfell

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description: MWSE Lua version of Combat Enhanced.
State.Name: Combat Enhanced - MWSE Edition

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: Replaces pearls with HD models and textures. Includes OAAB_Data pearls and new pearl varieties. Optional add-on adds new pearl-themed items to the game.
State.Name: Lustrous Pearls

State.Author: Merlord Greatness7 MelchiorDahrk
State.Description: Adds a fishing mechanic with over 25 species of fish and dynamic fishing animations.
State.Name: Ultimate Fishing

State.Author: superliuk
State.Description: An unnamed isle with an ancient barrow await you!
State.Name: Unnamed Isle

State.Author: chantox
State.Description: An essential tool in any nightblade's arsenal, Leech Effects adds a set of buffs that allow you to recover health, magicka, or fatigue when landing physical attacks.
State.Name: Leech Effects

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk and AFFA
State.Description: This mod adds Royal Imperial Mananaut Alberius outside of the Tower of Tel Fyr. He has a message that he wants you to deliver for him. At the end of the quest, you'll get your very own royal mananaut outfit!
State.Name: The Mananaut's Message

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Expands UI functionality with searching, filtering, and more visual feedback.
State.Name: UI Expansion

State.Author: Ruffin Vangarr
State.Description: Adds Sacred Necromancer armor to the game, used by the ordained ancestral mages of the Tribunal Temple.
State.Name: Sacred Necromancer Armor

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: This mod lets the player take control of the Suran Temple once they advance enough in the Tribunal Temple faction. Through a series of quests (and with some choices to make along the way), you will get to improve the temple.
State.Name: Temple Master

State.Author: The AATL Team
State.Description: Tamrielic Lore is a book in vanilla Morrowind that describes various artifacts seen throughout Morrowind. An Addendum to Tamrielic Lore seeks to expand upon Morrowind's artifacts list, while adding more quests, items, and artifacts that reflect previous TES titles. This is the resource page for AATL, which contains all new resources used in AATL.
State.Name: AATL Data - An Addendum to Tamrielic Lore Data

State.Author: Caeris
State.Description: Introduces five new quests to investigate the Order of the Black Worm's presence in Vvardenfell.
State.Name: God of Worms

State.Author: AlandroSul
State.Description: Meet four companions with full main quest commentary, new quests, and a new tavern to visit.
State.Name: The Strider's Nest - Companions and Quests

State.Author: PikachunoTM
State.Description: A merchant has set up shop outside of Vivek. Talk with him, and after some time he will ask you for some help with a personal matter from his past.
State.Name: A Merchant's Whim

State.Author: Sephumbra
State.Description: A MWSE lua library that may be required by other mods. It does nothing on its own.
State.Name: Seph's Library

State.Author: PikachunoTM
State.Description: Re-make of my old mod, Bucklers in Morrowind. Now version 2.0!
State.Name: Bucklers Remastered

State.Author: Aracelliy
State.Description:
Brings Morrowind combat into the next generation!  

100% chance to hit with all attributes and skills in the game are still useful with 100% hit!

Complete compatibility - no patches needed for weapon, race, NPC mods.

Unique and interesting weapon perks to make combat more interesting!

Works with ranged weapons and all NPCs/crea
State.Name: Next Generation Combat

State.Author: VitruvianGuar
State.Description: MWSE-lua mod, which enhances speechcraft skill via new gameplay mechanics and UI elements.
State.Name: Silver Tongue

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Implements the magicka regen functionality of Class-Conscious Character Progression (CCCP), without any of that mod's other features.
State.Name: CCCP Magicka Regen

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: Adds Wands to Morrowind. Fully functional wands enchanted as normal, cast-on-strike weapons. Staves also can shoot projectiles now, too!
State.Name: Wands

State.Author: Stripes
State.Description: made at the last minute for Summer Modjam 2020
State.Name: Ashlander Huntress Companion

State.Author: VitruvianGuar
State.Description: MWSE-lua overhaul of trade system with new gameplay and UI functionality for Mercantile skill
State.Name: Buying Game

State.Author: VitruvianGuar
State.Description: MWSE-lua mod, which fixes gameplay and interface inconsistencies in alchemy menu, provides it with built-in effect filter and implements Skyrim-like system for remembering ingredient effects.
State.Name: Alchemical Knowledge

State.Author: tewlwolow
State.Description: A weather overhaul with randomised cloud textures, more dynamic weathers, weather changes in interiors, seasonal weather chances, daytime hours changing with latitude and season, varied rain/snow density, dynamic cloud speeds etc.
State.Name: Watch the Skies

State.Author: Safebox - requested by RuffinVangarr
State.Description: Adds armour slots facepaint, eyewear, nosewear, lipwear, earwear, and headwear without removing the hair.
State.Name: Onion - Layered Headwear and Facial Wear

State.Author: Stripes
State.Description: MWSE Enhanced Healer Companion
State.Name: MWSE Enhanced Healer Companion

State.Author: Vizaru
State.Description: A balanced and diverse birthsign mod that expands the constellation into 27 birthsigns that are mechanically powerful and thematically unique.
State.Name: Moonlight - Birthsigns of Morrowind

State.Author: Istreddify
State.Description: This mod adds a Redoran lighthouse to the north-eastern coast of Vvardenfell.
State.Name: Ald Gash - a Redoran Lighthouse

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: The Crafting Framework is library that allows modders to quickly and easily implement complex crafting mechanics in Morrowind.
State.Name: The Crafting Framework

State.Author: Siltocyn
State.Description: Pluginless mwse-lua armor rebalancer using properties based on hollaajith's Armor Overhaul.
State.Name: Armor Auto-Balancer

State.Author: JosephMcKean
State.Description: Shop Affordable Home Furnishings & Home Goods with Furniture Catalogue!
State.Name: Furniture Catalogue

State.Author: tewlwolow
State.Description: Travel to Khuul and investigate the rumors about a smuggling operation nearby. Or perhaps it's more than that?
State.Name: A Cold Cell

State.Author: KirbonatedBeverage
State.Description: A library/code module that adds support for a perk system, a la the fallout games
State.Name: MWSE Perk Framework

State.Author: Hrnchamd
State.Description: Regional weather colours, skies and lighting. Visual weather editor and region-based presets. Seamless transitions between regions. Share your presets.
State.Name: Weather Adjuster

State.Author: rfuzzo
State.Description: This mod adds compare tooltips for looked-at or equipped items against the equipped item of the same category. The mod has multiple MCM options to configure the comparison style.
State.Name: MWSE Compare Tooltips

State.Author: AdituV and VitruvianGuar
State.Description: Makes locks and traps detection a random chance based on the player's Security skill. Requires lates version of MWSE.
State.Name: Locks and Traps Detection

State.Author: Sephumbra
State.Description: A MWSE mod that makes almost every element of the HUD customizable to a certain degree.
State.Name: Seph's HUD Customizer

State.Author: Sephumbra
State.Description: A MWSE mod that lets you soul trap NPCs.
State.Name: Seph's NPC Soul Trapping

State.Author: Merlord and Danae
State.Description: Adds starting equipment, based on the items seen in the images in the class selection screen for vanilla classes, or on major/minor skills for custom classes. Compatible with Chargen Revamped - Expanded Lands (CREL). Uses MWSE/Lua.
State.Name: Merlord's Starting Equipment

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: akh
State.Description: Expands armor restrictions to other Indoril armor pieces and adds configurable conditions under which player is allowed to wear the armor in public.
State.Name: Sanctioned Indoril Armor

State.Author: Zilophos and Spammer21
State.Description: This mod uses the power of MWSE-Lua to provide players with an in-game item editor.
State.Name: Zilophos' Item Editor

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description:
Picture this: You are in a middle of a fight, swinging a bound longsword, when suddenly it vanishes right from your hand. The cast time is up, and because you had no idea how much time you had left, you're now defenseless against your opponnents!

 Frustrating, isn't it?

 This mod intends to give you a visual idea of how much time you stil
State.Name: Effects Timers - MWSE

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: KirbonatedBeverage
State.Description: Completely overhauls character progression with a new XP system, perks, and new level up UI
State.Name: Kirbonated Character Progression

State.Author: Danae
State.Description: Adds DRIP integration to 40+ mods
State.Name: Danaes DRIP Depot

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: Obtain a spell to teleport to the Astral Pocket, a small pocket realm that a Telvanni wizard has found himself lost in.
State.Name: OAAB - The Astral Pocket

State.Author: baronnolanvonstraya
State.Description: Adds a roaving merchant caravan that constantly moves between the major towns of Vvardenfell.
State.Name: Markets and Caravans

State.Author: ZaMothman
State.Description: A Redoran wizard wants five items to remember his dead wife. An epic hunt of searching sewers, caves, rivers, all for a reward of Septims.
State.Name: Redoran Heat - A Necromancer's Sorrow

State.Author: stormless
State.Description: Welcome Home adds 28 immersive dwellings throughout Vvardenfell, available through purchase, trade, or quest. Compatible with, but does not require, Morrowind Rebirth 5.0.
State.Name: Welcome Home

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: This shows the player's name, race, class, level, and location to the popular app, Discord.
State.Name: Discord Rich Presence for Morrowind

State.Author: Krimson
State.Description: Adds a fully functional Gray Cowl of Nocturnal to the game, with a quest to discover the identity of The Gray Fox!
State.Name: The Gray Fox

State.Author: Remiros
State.Description: Discover the remnants of a failed Telvanni expedition and explore the depths of Bethaleft, a Dwemer citadel that served as a testing ground for the Tools of Kagrenac.
State.Name: The Vestige of Bethaleft

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Automatically hides your drugs so you don't have to dump them on the floor in order to trade. Uses MWSE, no plugin required.
State.Name: MWSE Hide the Skooma

Original.Name: Customizable MWSE Multi Mark and Harder Recall-47065-2-1-8-1623167983.7z

State.Author: Virnetch
State.Description:
An overhaul of the mark and recall system using MWSE 2.1 to allow:

 - Multiple mark locations, even from other mods. Teleport companions to your location. Limit number of marks by mysticism.

 - Higher magicka cost and lower cast chance for long recall distances.

 - Limited number of daily recalls. 

Features can be changed in MCM
State.Name: Customizable MWSE Multi Mark and Harder Recall

State.Author: AliceL93
State.Description: This mod gives you the opportunity to join the Census and Excise Office and do quests for them. Part of the May Modathon Month.
State.Name: Census and Excise Office Faction

State.Author: Stripes
State.Description: As the title implies, this mod makes the Dark Brotherhood assassins relentless in their pursuit to murder you.
State.Name: Relentless Dark Brotherhood

State.Author: R-Zero
State.Description: Makes the Willpower stat less fucking useless by fixing the spell resist mechanics. Requires MWSE 2.1-dev.
State.Name: Putting Power In Willpower 2 - Antimagic Boogaloo

State.Author: Caeris
State.Description: Introduces five new quests to investigate the Order of the Black Worm's presence in Vvardenfell.
State.Name: God of Worms

State.Author: Petethegoat
State.Description: Uses MWSE Lua to add an Oblivion style ownership indicator, when you look at owned items, beds, and more.
State.Name: Ownership Indicator

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description:
Introduces a backstabbing mechanic - do more damage when stabbing an enemy from behind (based on Agility/Sneak). Mod Configuration Menu includes option for Short Blades only or all weapons. Be warned - NPCs can backstab you as well!





Uses the latest development version of MWSE, not OpenMW compatible.
State.Name: Brutal Backstabbing

State.Author: Kalinter aka KJS94
State.Description: This is a long overdue update to my Broadsheets and Notice Boards mod from 2015. Overhauls quests and rewrites documents from the original mod, adds new documents, fixes bugs, and adds a few other features. Now requires OAAB_Data and Tamriel_Data.
State.Name: Broadsheets and Notice Boards Redone

State.Author: Istreddify
State.Description: A small tower near Old Ebonheart you can buy for 3000 gold.
State.Name: Old Ebonheart Alchemist's Tower

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Changes the difficulty slider as the player levels up or moves through the world.
State.Name: Dynamic Difficulty

State.Author: Sephumbra
State.Description: A simple MWSE mod that adds more detailed health, magicka and fatigue bars to any npc or creature you look at.
State.Name: Seph's Enemy Bars

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description:
Adds a Hotbar to the game with all your hotkeys displayed.



v1.2 should be the final version. Have fun!
State.Name: QuickKeys Hotbar - MWSE

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: JosephMcKean
State.Description: Press Alt to tell your follower to come towards you so they don’t block the doorway.
State.Name: Come To Me

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: A tool for automatically patching conflicts between mods for TES3: Morrowind.
State.Name: TES3Merge

State.Author: Markond
State.Description: The disused catacombs under Balmora make a fine spot for a flea market. Food, drink, jewellery, home goods, tailoring, all available and guaranteed watched over by the sacred dead.
State.Name: Balmora Gravemarket

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Assigns ownership to the many, many items and containers that rightly should be owned but weren't, and otherwise makes adjustments to item ownership.
State.Name: Ownership Overhaul

State.Author: Denis418
State.Description: You can now buy a house in Andothren, the biggest Hlaalu port on the Inner Sea added by the Dominions of Dust release of Tamriel Rebuilt.
State.Name: Tamriel Rebuilt Andothren House for Sale

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: Adds a few new, simple, combat mechanics to improve combat variety: combat scavenging for NPCs, disarming (and being disarmed), as well as bystanders that will sometimes flee or assist in some situations.
State.Name: Simple Combat Mechanics

State.Author: mort
State.Description: Adds a number of features to being Grandmaster of House Redoran, including master level trainers, a teleportation ring, and the ability to covertly join another House.
State.Name: Redoran Archmaster Perks

State.Author: AliceL93
State.Description: An Ordinator follower named Elisamsi with her own backstory. Commentary on quests and some character development.
State.Name: Elisamsi Follower

State.Author: ZaMothman
State.Description: Player home near Big Head's Shack in Sheogorad at the Sea of Ghosts.
State.Name: Ghost Hunt - Domain of Ghosts

State.Author: efrost
State.Description: Highlights: Select merchants restock glass and ebony arrows, arrows have a 75% chance of recovery, and the bound longbow uses bound arrows.
State.Name: FMO Marksman

State.Author: ModManSam
State.Description:
Add reputation gain to Fighters Guild, Imperial Legion and Thieves Guild quests.



Most faction questlines reward you with reputation, but it's mysteriously missing from the fighter's guild, imperial legion and thieves guild. This mod aims to rectify this oversight.
State.Name: Reputation Fixes

State.Author: OperatorJack and AliceL93
State.Description: Adds a new power named 'Call Incarnate' which summons a Failed Incarnate of the Nerevarine to fight alongside you. The mod also overhauls the Failed Incarnate NPCs in the Cavern of Incarnate.
State.Name: Call Incarnate

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: Channel your inner Thief and douse light sources with your bow, crossbow, or thrown weapons.
State.Name: Douse the Lights

Original.Meta:
[General]
gameName=Morrowind
gameFile=Data Files\Sound\Vo\Misc\Dagoth Ur Welcome D.mp3
Original.Name: Data Files_Sound_Vo_Misc_Dagoth Ur Welcome D.mp3

State.Author: NullCascade
State.Description: Have issues with the game crashing on exit? This might help!
State.Name: Expeditious Exit

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description:
Allows you to give basic orders to your summoned creatures. 

Adds a new spell, called "Soul Release", allowing you to summon a soul trapped in a soulgem. You can now have Vivec or Almalexia as obedient summons! 

Requires Magicka Expanded.
State.Name: Obedient Summons - MWSE

State.Author: Merlord
State.Description: A simple quality of life MWSE mod that allows you to use the keyboard to scroll through vertical scroll pane buttons.
State.Name: Key Scroller

State.Author: chantox
State.Description: Burial Obols adds a new way to boost your luck by adding lucky coins to ancestral tombs. A single lucky coin will be distributed to a fixed (and configurable) amount of random tombs throughout the world, so every single run is different. Try and find them all! (If you're into grave robbing, that is).
State.Name: Burial Obols

State.Author: abot
State.Description: Makes companions (the ones with the short companion local variable set to 1) able to interact with possible loot sources and doors you Alt+Activate, can fix/improve some companions/followers features, detect abot's modded Scenic Travelling and apply it to followers not already compatible with it...
State.Name: Smart Companions

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: Using MWSE Lua and Magicka Expanded, embark on a short quest to gain the power of transmuting items into gold: Chrysopoeia. Search for the most learned alchemist on the island of Morrowind to find it. But, remember, nothing is free.
State.Name: Chrysopoeia

State.Author: OperatorJack
State.Description: This mod overhauls Drethan Ancestral Tomb, transforming it into a much larger location that can be used as a player home after completing the quest, "The Weary Vampire."
State.Name: The Weary Vampire

State.Author: thevampman242
State.Description: A small Quest/Dungeon mod to find some relics of saints from Cryodiil made in honor of the 2022 May Modathon and Morrowind's 20TH anniversary.
State.Name: Saint Heist

State.Author: Irisie
State.Description: In the Sea of Ghost lies a tomb to a great warrior, visit his grotto and enjoy his wealth.
State.Name: Jurgar's Treasure

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: Melchior Dahrk
State.Description: Adds a Daedric helm bearing the aspect of Azura which you can acquire through a new quest which starts at the Holamayan Monastery near the Shrine of Azura. Explore the hidden depths below the shrine to become the Champion of Azura!
State.Name: Aspect of Azura

State.Author: PF Cacklefanny
State.Description: Adds a new dungeon in Molag Amur Region (10, -6) for characters at or above level 10.
State.Name: Hiram's Rest

State.Author: super1422223
State.Description: A simple mod that adds Fortune Tellers to the game, who can be paid to read your future and randomly bestow a temporary buff or debuff to you. Different fortune tellers provide different buffs and debuffs. These effects can range from being very beneficial to very detrimental, though not all affect you in such a major way.
State.Name: Immersive Omens and Fortune Tellers

State.Author: a deadly donut
State.Description: Replaces a shipwreck south of Seyda Neen with a livable ship, complete with food, beds, and a fast-travelling Shipmaster. Also adds some mid-tier enemy NPCs to fight. Can be found directly south of the Imperial Dock in Seyda Neen or travelled to from the docks at Ebonheart, Gnaar Mok, and Dagon Fel.
State.Name: Smuggler's Outset Island

State.Author: Dillonn241
State.Description: This is a simple mod that speeds up character creation to the time it takes you to make your character.
State.Name: Quick Character Creation

State.Author: Half11
State.Description: This mod fixes Bethesda's overly enthusiastic expansion hooks by delaying the Dark Brotherhood attacks (for Tribunal) and limiting intrustive dialogue topics to a few NPCs (Bloodmoon).
State.Name: Expansion Delay

State.Author: MrAA
State.Description: A small free house located in Seyda Neen
State.Name: Seyda Neen House

Original.Name: Vodunius Nuccius Gives You His House-51748-1-9-1660935731.7z

State.Author: FelsenSethandus
State.Description: Vodunius Nuccius Gives You His House
State.Name: Vodunius Nuccius Gives You His House

State.Author: super1422223
State.Description: A set of gear and a very short quest to obtain it to help new players or give new characters a little edge. Comes with enchantments great for exploring underwater locations, and a nice new set of medium armor because there isn't enough of it in this game
State.Name: The Submariner

State.Author: seibaby
State.Description: All those boring urns in ancestral tombs that normally only have Bonemeal in them now occasionally yield some leveled loot. Most commonly, Gravedust, but sometimes a nice little enchanted trinket or gem.
State.Name: Urn Your Blings

State.Author: RandomPal
State.Description: Modlist focused on location and dungeon mods
State.Name: An alternative to Morrowind Rebirth - A modlist by RandomPal

State.Author: mort
State.Description: Rebuilds stealth mechanics from the ground up, and makes sneaking a viable playstyle
State.Name: Stealth Improved

State.Author: Spammer
State.Description: Adds a buyable spell called "Enchant Drain", that allows you to use your enchanted staves and amulets as a supplementary mana pool for the duration of the spell.
State.Name: Enchant Drain - MWSE

State.Author: Mesafoo
State.Description:
Tweaked version of Mesafoo's Companion HealthBars, showing Magicka, Fatigue as well as currently selected weapon.

Also, added compatibility with Seph's HUD customizer.
State.Name: More Detailed Companion HealthBars MWSE Lua Script

State.Author: Remiros
State.Description: Adds skills requirements for weapons and armors.
State.Name: Equipment Requirements

State.Author: JohnMoonsugar
State.Description: mlox is a tool for analyzing and sorting your plugin load order.
State.Name: mlox

State.Author: Xero Foxx
State.Description: Adds over 500 hidden containers for you to find in the sea for every region around the island of Vvardenfell. Each contains random items that change for EVERY playthrough. Randomization is weighted for balanced distribution.
State.Name: Hidden Sea Loot

State.Author: Aphiteth
State.Description: The Museum of Artifacts' display tables are being damaged by the weight of Stendarr's Hammer, so they're looking to sell it! Should you buy the hammer, you will open a new questline. Be warned, eyes are watching the museum and the hammer.
State.Name: A Legend Restored - Stendarr's Hammer

State.Author: AliceL93 - Caeris - Lucas9 and Curmudgeon
State.Description: A complete overhaul of the Thieves' Guild faction. New quests, tweaks for existing quests, items, and a lot more!
State.Name: Thieves' Guild Overhaul

State.Author: Vizaru
State.Description: An immersive and balanced race mod that gives each race two named passives and one daily power. All designed to feel fun while remaining lore friendly.
State.Name: Reincarnate - Races of Morrowind

Original.Name: Goldbrand Reforged - The Quest for Eltonbrand-52277-1-00-1675581815.7z

State.Author: Discontinuous Qualia
State.Description: Brave the dangers of Vvardenfell in this lore-friendly quest mod to reforge Goldbrand into the mysterious Eltonbrand. Speak to Sirilonwe in the Vivec Mages Guild while carrying Goldbrand to begin the quest. Part of the 2023 Winter Modjam.
State.Name: Goldbrand Reforged - The Quest for Eltonbrand

State.Author: OAAB_Data Team
State.Description: This page will be used to upload minor mods which integrate content from OAAB_Data into the game by the OAAB team.
State.Name: OAAB Integrations

State.Author: ProfArmitage
State.Description: Join the Thieves Guild after completing the Fighters Guild code book quest, if you've completed one other task as well.
State.Name: Thieves Guild Regained Trust

State.Author: Aphiteth
State.Description: After the "Dreams of a White Guar" quest is completed, the White Guar will reveal itself to the player at specific locations around the Grazelands Region and, it will reward the player by becoming a new companion that scales to the players level, up to 30.
State.Name: Visions of the White Guar - A Versatile Companion

State.Author: Necrolesian
State.Description: Places one copy of each adamantium armor piece (except the helm) in Vvardenfell. They're not for sale.
State.Name: Adamantium Armor Integrated

State.Author: Petethegoat
State.Description: Few people are blessed to know the hour or the location of their death. And some people will defy even the foreknowledge of CHIM.
State.Name: The Icarian Incident

State.Author: Petethegoat
State.Description: Automatically mirrors the inventory icons of left gloves, pauldrons, etc.
State.Name: Left Gloves User Interface

State.Author: Lucevar
State.Description: A new merchant has come to Gnisis, selling potions of jump to would-be fast travelers. A pilgrim has gone missing. Are these two things as unrelated as they might seem? A small quest mod, suitable for low level characters.
State.Name: Leap of Faith

Original.Name: Not So Simple Balmora Player Home-46574-3-2-1615581832.zip

State.Author: deleted14075335
State.Description: Featuring a withdrawn abode above the spymaster for the player to "avoid unwanted attention." Simple and sparse as it begins, but just like the player with potential. Decorate, customize, add loot and spoil during your playthrough. This is a reworking of a player home mod by Pastagon. Ownership/script/GMST fixed version of the original mod here too
State.Name: Simpler Balmora Player Home

State.Author: AliceL93
State.Description: This mod lets you do more quests for the Ashlander tribes. Ideal for roleplaying. Part of the May Modathon Month.
State.Name: Ashlander Quests

State.Description: Adds over 500 hidden containers for you to find in the sea for every region around the island of Vvardenfell. Each contains random items that change for EVERY playthrough. Randomization is weighted for balanced distribution.

State.Description:
Explore the seedier side of how the Temple wields power. Hear the latest rumors from the residents of Necrom, who complain of a marital dispute that has disturbed the silence of the City Above.
